  HeaderLine: Which of the following statements about multidisciplinary management
    in gastric cancer is most accurate?
  AsnwerSlot:
  - Surgery alone determines treatment planning in most cases
  - Management is optimized through multidisciplinary discussion involving surgery,
    medical oncology, pathology, radiology, and gastroenterology
  - MDT discussion is only useful in metastatic disease
  - ) Pathology review has limited impact on treatment strategy
  IsCorrectAnswer: 00010000
  Reference: ) Pathology review has limited impact on treatment strategy
